      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "A PERFECT DANCE (3) brings some decent from from Albion Park where she was fourth from the back row two back and finished runner-up last month. Has the benefit of a good draw. Finds a nice race and may take beating. Former WA pacer WELEASE WODDEWICK (4) made a winning start in Queensland, coming from the back row and getting home by 2 metres at this venue two weeks ago. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Could go on with it. CANADIAN LASS NZ (8) draws on the second line this time but is hard to knock after winning her last two outings here. MY ULTIMATE FELIX (9) has been getting closer to the winner with each start lately and could be ready to strike after a 1.7m second at Albion Park last tine.",
